GEYSERS POWER PLANT
The Geysers Power Plant is located in the Geysers Geothermal Area of the Mayacmas Mountains in Sonoma and Lake Counties, approximately 27 miles northeast of Healdsburg.
Several rivers, including Big Sulphur Creek, Little Sulphur Creek, Hot Springs Creek, Bear Canyon Creek, Squaw Creek, and Andersen Creek, flow through the Geysers area.
The land in this area is principally used for the exploration, development and utilization of geothermal energy.
Other land uses in the area primarily include recreation and mining.
Recreation is generally restricted to large deer-hunting clubs and smaller parcels of land with cabins scattered throughout the area.
Mining is for aggregate and gold and used to include mercury mining.
Operations at the Geysers Power Plant began in 1960.
